text:
Hey Luke, please meet Erin your incredible E-Mentor we've been telling you about :smile:.  Feel free to introduce yourselves, say a little bit about what you would like to get out of the mentorship and continue chatting within this channel. :wave:

I will now be leaving the channel, but please direct message myself or penny-prospela if you have any questions. All the best for now! :slightly_smiling_face:

Dear Mr. Nash,

My name is Luke Vuilliomenet from the Prospela E-Mentoring program. I wanted to send a quick greeting and introduce myself after receiving your profile.

As mentioned before, my name is Luke Vuilliomenet, and I am a first-year M.F.A. Visual Effects Student at the Savannah College of Art and Design (SCAD). I specialize in Houdini FX, technical direction, and C.G. Lighting, intending to join a studio after my graduation to work in advertisement and possibly feature film.

An essential part of receiving my degree is a thesis presented at the end of the course. Part of this thesis is a committee of three people, chosen from within the school, and intended industry with approval. The three individuals act as guides/mentors and evaluators of the project.

I would ask if you would be willing to work with me in the creation of my thesis, followed by joining the committee when formed in roughly a year?

I greatly appreciate you taking the time to consider mentoring my thesis work and look forward to working with you.
Hey Luke. I can't be sure where a year will take me but let's start chatting! Can you tell me more about the thesis project and what your plan is?
